The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	Aryadahas papers for the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB)s annual general meeting on Friday, were not found to be in order following which Sultan Ahmed and Tushar Sarkar were called for a hearing on Wednesday. Ahmed was to represent Aryadaha at the AGM while Tushar Sarkar was to attend the working committee meetings. The other 119 members papers were found to be in order after scrutiny.      
	CAB joint secretary, Biswarup Dey, said: Theres a dispute over Aryadahas papers as they were found to be incomplete. Meanwhile, Chinmoy Roy, who was Bengals fitness trainer in the last season, may lose his job as a certain section of the CAB are not interested in continuing with him.                
	 Churchill Brothers of Goa have confirmed that they will be participating in the upcoming IFA Shield, said IFA secretary Utpal Ganguli on Monday.       
	There was some initial hesitation from Churchill, but they have confirmed that they will be playing in the Shield, he said.                
	 The 59th State Athletics Championship will be held from July 29 to August 1 at the Salt Lake Stadium and the Sports Authority of India, Eastern Centre.                                                                                                                                                                       
